AAA.name: Unit net weight
AAA.desc:
[6160] Weight (mass) of goods including any packing normally going
                                    with them to a buyer in a retail sale.

AAB.name: Unit gross weight
AAB.desc:
[6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the
                                    carrier's equipment.

AAC.name: Total net weight
AAC.desc: Total weight of goods excluding packaging.

AAD.name: Total gross weight
AAD.desc:
[6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the
                                    carrier's equipment.

AAE.name: Item gross weight
AAE.desc: Gross weight at line item level.

AAF.name: Net net weight
AAF.desc: [6048] Weight (mass) of the goods themselves without any packing.

AAG.name: Stern thrust
AAG.desc: Force exerted by a thruster installed at the stern of a vessel.

AAH.name: Bow thrust
AAH.desc: Force exerted by a thruster installed at the bow of a vessel.

AAI.name: Hydrate content of an alcoholic product at bottling
AAI.desc: The hydrate content of an alcoholic product at the moment of bottling.

AAJ.name: Number of units per pallet
AAJ.desc: The number of units contained on a pallet.

AAK.name: Fat content
AAK.desc: An indication of the fat content of a product.

AAL.name: Net weight
AAL.desc:
[6160] Weight (mass) of goods including any packing normally going
                                    with them to a buyer in a retail sale.

AAM.name: Gross tonnage of the vessel
AAM.desc:
[6300] The measure of the overall size of a ship determined in
                                    accordance with the provisions of the International Convention on Tonnage
                                    Measurement of Ships, 1969.

AAN.name: Net tonnage of the vessel
AAN.desc:
[6302] The measure of the useful capacity of a ship determined in
                                    accordance with the provisions of the International Convention on Tonnage
                                    Measurement of Ships, 1969.

AAP.name: Voltage
AAP.desc:
Electromotive force, or difference of electronic potential between two
                                    points.

AAR.name: Heat dissipation
AAR.desc: Measurement of the rate of dispersal of heat.

AAS.name: Air flow
AAS.desc: Measurement of the flow of air.

AAT.name: Shock impact
AAT.desc: Measurement of the impact of a shock.

AAU.name: Operative temperature
AAU.desc:
Temperature identified system or process works according to
                                    specifications.

AAV.name: Non operative temperature
AAV.desc:
Temperature identified system or process does not work according to
                                    specifications.

AAW.name: Gross volume
AAW.desc:
The observed volume unadjusted for factors such as temperature or
                                    gravity.

AAX.name: Net volume
AAX.desc:
The observed volume after adjustment for factors such as temperature
                                    or gravity.

ABF.name: Item width when unrolled
ABF.desc: The width of an item when unrolled.

ABG.name: Item length when unrolled
ABG.desc: The length of an item when unrolled.

ABH.name: Item area when unrolled
ABH.desc: The area occupied by an item when unrolled.

ABI.name: Original wort
ABI.desc:
Measure of the malt and hops content of beer, before fermentation has
                                    taken place.

ABJ.name: Volume
ABJ.desc:
The amount of air space taken up by the entity identified in the 6311
                                    qualifier.

ABL.name: Peg hole horizontal distance from package leftmost edge
ABL.desc:
Horizontal distance from the left most edge of the package to the
                                    center of the hole into which the peg is inserted.

ABM.name: Peg hole vertical distance from package top
ABM.desc:
Vertical distance from the top of the package to the top of the hole
                                    into which the peg is inserted.

ABN.name: Number of layers per pallet
ABN.desc: The number of layers per pallet.

ABO.name: Product strengh, chemical
ABO.desc: The amount of the single active chemical ingredient within a product.

ABP.name: Product strength basis, chemical
ABP.desc:
Amount of product used as the basis for the specification of the
                                    chemical product strenght.

ABT.name: Payload weight, maximum
ABT.desc: The maximum weight of a payload.

ABY.name: Conveyance summer dead weight
ABY.desc: Registered summer dead weight total tonnage of the vessel.

ABZ.name: Containerized cargo on vessel's weight
ABZ.desc: Total weight of containerized cargo on vessel.

ACA.name: Non-containerized cargo on vessel's weight
ACA.desc: Total weight of non-containerized cargo on vessel.

ACE.name: Weight ascertained
ACE.desc:
[4240] Endorsement of the true weight (mass) as ascertained or
                                    verified by the railway (CIM 81).

ACG.name: Chargeable weight
ACG.desc: The weight on which charges are based.

ACN.name: Estimated gross weight
ACN.desc:
Estimated weight (mass) of goods, including packing and excluding
                                    carrier's.

ACP.name: Estimated volume
ACP.desc: Estimated size or measure of anything in three dimensions.

ACS.name: Vessel overall length
ACS.desc: Total overall length of the vessel.

ACV.name: Loading meters
ACV.desc:
The length in a vehicle, whereby the complete width and height over
                                    that length is needed for the goods.

ACW.name: Number of axles
ACW.desc: Number of axles of movable equipment or means of transport on wheels.

ACX.name: Payload
ACX.desc: The revenue-producing load carried by a means of transport.

ADR.name: Start position in the length
ADR.desc:
The starting position from the beginning of an item located in the
                                    length direction.

ADS.name: End position in the length
ADS.desc:
The end position from the beginning of an item located in the length
                                    direction.

ADT.name: Start position in the width
ADT.desc:
The start position from the beginning of an item located in the width
                                    direction.

ADU.name: End position in the width
ADU.desc:
The end position from the beginning of an item located in the width
                                    direction.

ADV.name: Start position in the thickness
ADV.desc:
The start position from the beginning of an item located in the
                                    thickness direction.

ADW.name: End position in the thickness
ADW.desc:
The end position from the beginning of an item located in the
                                    thickness direction.

ADX.name: Transport container actual filling weight
ADX.desc: Actual filling weight of a transport container.

ADY.name: Transport container maximum capacity
ADY.desc: Maximum capacity of a transport container.

ADZ.name: Declared net weight
ADZ.desc:
The declared net weight of a product or products used for invoicing,
                                    customs or transport purposes.

AEA.name: Loading height
AEA.desc:
Maximum height of products or packages loaded onto a given
                                    transportation device or equipment such as a pallet.

AEB.name: Stacking height
AEB.desc:
Maximum height up to which the same product or package may be placed
                                    one upon the other for storage purposes.

AEC.name: Calculated weight
AEC.desc: The calculated weight of the item based on the ordered dimensions.

AEE.name: Impurity
AEE.desc:
The impurity of the product i.e. the measurement of other chemical
                                    elements not normally appearing in a product.

AEI.name: Drained weight
AEI.desc:
The weight of a product when all liquids used in the packaging of the
                                    product have been removed.

AEL.name: Area
AEL.desc: Extent or measure of a surface.

AEM.name: Equipment storage limitation
AEM.desc: Maximum storage limit of the equipment.

AEN.name: Radioactive index of transport
AEN.desc:
The index of transport determines the maximum radiation level at a
                                    distance of 1m from the external surface.

AEP.name: Average gross weight
AEP.desc:
Weight which is the outcome of the division of the total gross weight
                                    by the number of units.

AEQ.name: Forward draft
AEQ.desc:
Depth of water from the surface of water to the bottom of the vessel
                                    measured at the draft mark of the bow.

AER.name: After draft
AER.desc:
Depth of water from the surface of water to the bottom of the vessel
                                    measured at the draft mark of the stern.

AET.name: Transport equipment gross weight
AET.desc:
Weight of a transport equipment including the cargo and carrier's
                                    equipment.

AEU.name: Total transport equipment gross weight
AEU.desc:
Total weight of all transport equipment including the cargo and
                                    carrier's equipment.

AEW.name: Penetrometry
AEW.desc: Measurement of force required to drive a standard penetrating stamp.

AEX.name: Durofel
AEX.desc: Measurement of the elastic force using a standard penetrating stamp.

AEY.name: Juice weight per 100 grams
AEY.desc:
Measurement of weight of juice, based on 100 grams of the entire
                                    weight.

AEZ.name: Fruit skin colour
AEZ.desc: Measurement of the colouring of the epidermis of a fruit.

AFA.name: Fixed incremental measurement
AFA.desc: The measurement of the fixed increment.

AFB.name: Durofel D10
AFB.desc:
Measure of the elastic force of the pulp of a fruit. It is measured
                                    with a penetrating stamp with diameter 10.

AFC.name: Durofel D25
AFC.desc:
Measure of the elastic force of the pulp of a fruit. It is measured
                                    with a penetrating stamp with diameter 25.

AFD.name: Durofel D50
AFD.desc:
Measure of the elastic force of the pulp of a fruit. It is measured
                                    with a penetrating stamp with diameter 50.

AFE.name: Maximum stacking weight
AFE.desc:
The maximum weight which may be stacked upon a product or package
                                    without the product or packaging being crushed.

AFF.name: Gross measure cube
AFF.desc:
The total cubic space occupied by an item, taking into account any
                                    protruding components, arrived at by multiplying the maximum length, width and
                                    height.

AFG.name: Percentage fat content in dry matter
AFG.desc: The percentage of fat content in dry matter.

AFH.name: Saccharometric content
AFH.desc: Measurement of the sugar content of a solution.

AFI.name: Hydrate content of an alcoholic product after bottling
AFI.desc:
The hydrate content which occurs in an alcoholic product after
                                    bottling.

BMY.name: Platinum
BMY.desc: The measurement of the platinum component.

BMZ.name: Silver
BMZ.desc: The measurement of the silver component.

BNA.name: List
BNA.desc:
The leaning or inclination of a vessel expressed in degrees port or
                                    starboard.

BNB.name: Trim
BNB.desc: The condition of a vessel with reference to its longitudinal axis.

BNC.name: Free water
BNC.desc:
The volume of water present in a container that is not in suspension
                                    in the contained liquid.

BNE.name: API (American Petroleum Institute) gravity
BNE.desc:
The relative density of petroleum liquids as specified by a standard
                                    developed by the API.

BNF.name: Petroleum gross observed volume
BNF.desc:
The total volume of all petroleum liquids and sediment and water,
                                    excluding free water, at observed temperature and pressure.

BNG.name: Petroleum gross standard volume
BNG.desc:
The total volume of all petroleum liquids, sediment, and water
                                    excluding free water, corrected by the appropriate volume correction factor for the
                                    observed temperature and American Petroleum Institute relative density, or density
                                    to a standard temperature.

BNH.name: Volume variance
BNH.desc: The change in the volume measurement.

BNI.name: Petroleum net standard volume
BNI.desc:
The total volume of all petroleum liquids, excluding sediment and
                                    water and free water, corrected by the appropriate volume correction factor for the
                                    observed temperature and American Petroleum Institute gravity relative to density or
                                    to a standard temperature.

BNJ.name: Material on-board quantity, after discharge
BNJ.desc:
The material in vessel tanks, void spaces, and pipelines after
                                    discharge.

BNK.name: Petroleum total calculated volume
BNK.desc:
The total volume of all petroleum liquids, sediment and water
                                    corrected by the appropriate volume correction factor for the observed temperature
                                    and American Petroleum Institute (API) gravity, relative density, or density to a
                                    standard temperature.

BNL.name: Petroleum total observed volume
BNL.desc:
The total volume of all petroleum liquids, sediment and water and free
                                    water at observed temperature and pressure.

BNM.name: Innage gauge distance
BNM.desc:
The measured distance from the surface of the liquid to a fixed datum
                                    plate or to the tank bottom.

BNN.name: Petroleum net standard weight
BNN.desc:
The total weight of all petroleum liquids excluding sediments, water
                                    and free water.

BNO.name: Sediment and water in petroleum
BNO.desc:
The measurement of non-hydrocarbon solid material and water in
                                    suspension in petroleum liquid.

BNP.name: Observed reference height, tank
BNP.desc:
The observed distance from the tank bottom or datum plate to the
                                    established reference point.

BNQ.name: Reference height, tank
BNQ.desc:
The measured distance from the tank bottom or datum plate to the
                                    established reference point.

BNR.name: Ullage gauge distance
BNR.desc:
The measured distance from the cargo liquid surface to the reference
                                    point.

BNS.name: Trim correction
BNS.desc:
The correction applied to the observed gauge or observed volume when a
                                    vessel is not on an even keel.

BNT.name: Bow to bridge distance
BNT.desc: The distance between the bow and the bridge of a vessel.

BSW.name: Breaking strength wet
BSW.desc: The measured breaking strength when wet.

CT.name: Contents of package
CT.desc:
In combination with the other data elements of the actual segment this
                                    code indicates the measured content of a package.

CV.name: Commercial weight
CV.desc: Item weight considering its maximum possible humidity.

CZ.name: Core length
CZ.desc: To specify length of core on which product is to be placed.

D.name: Destination weight agreement
D.desc:
The agreed weight of despatched goods whose weight may change during
                                    transport.

DR.name: Denier
DR.desc: The measured fineness of a material.

DW.name: Width, boxcar door
DW.desc: The measured width of a boxcar door.

FI.name: Filament count
FI.desc: Used e.g. in textile, print industries.

G.name: Gross weight
G.desc:
[6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the
                                    carrier's equipment.

LN.name: Length dimension
LN.desc: (6168) Length of pieces or packages stated for transport purposes.

MO.name: Moisture
MO.desc: Measurement application is the moisture content of the item.

N.name: Actual net weight
N.desc: The actual weight of the goods excluding packaging.

PRS.name: Pre stretch
PRS.desc:
Measurement identifying the amount an item has been stretched prior to
                                    use.

RJ.name: Rockwell C
RJ.desc: Hardness in the Rockwell C scale.

T.name: Tare weight
T.desc: Weight excluding goods and loose accessories.

TC.name: Temperature
TC.desc: A measurement in relation to temperature.

TN.name: Time period
TN.desc: Measurement of a specific length of time.

VH.name: Height, van door
VH.desc: The height of the door of a van or container.

VW.name: Width, van door
VW.desc: The width of the door of a van or container.

WA.name: Weight per unit of area
WA.desc: The weight per unit of an area.

WM.name: Width, maximum
WM.desc: The maximum distance from side to side.

WU.name: Weight per unit of length
WU.desc: The weight per unit of length.

XH.name: Side height, flat bed with removable sides
XH.desc: The height of the removable sides of a flat bed truck.

ZFS.name: Iron plus silicon
ZFS.desc: The measured substance iron plus silicon.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc:
A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and
                                    as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code
                                    list.
